==Finnish==
([[Wiktionary:Finnish_index_v|index V]])

===Noun===
'''vittu''' (Plural [[vitut]])

# (''vulgar slang'') [[cunt]], [[pussy]]
# (''ancient Finnish'') female genitalia

====Synonyms====
*(''female genitalia'') [[pillu]], [[tussu]], [[pimppi]]

====Usage notes====
*''Vittu'' means, as an intensifying word (in the genitive), approximately "fucking" as in ''vitun tyhmä'' "fucking stupid".

While vittu can mean both cunt and fuck, when a Finn calls someone cunt, they use words like [[huora]], [[narttu]] (female) or [[runkku]], [[kyrpä]] (male) instead of vittu.

The respective name for the male organ is ''[[kyrpä]]''. 

Some females may find the word ''vittu'' and its derivatives too pejorative, so they may want to use the word ''[[kyrpä]]'' and its derivatives instead, when possible.

